      "detail": "Unknown provenance reflects that the nominal custodian does not know their data has been intercepted, copied, or compromised. The state's copy of the data has no visible provenance trail in the custodian's systems. This invisibility is what makes the custody defeat particularly insidious compared to overt data theft. Unknown provenance means the nominal custodian cannot even assess the scope of the custody compromise."
    },
